  summary "microRNAs (miRNAs) are short (20-24 nt) non-coding RNAs that are
 involved in post-transcriptional regulation of gene expression in
 multicellular organisms by affecting both the stability and translation of
 target mRNAs. This microRNA represents the most abundant miRNA in the corneal
 and lens epithelia of the eye and has been shown to interfere with target
 binding by another miRNA, miR-205. Through regulation of the VEGF and Akt
 signaling pathways, this microRNA may inhibit corneal angiogenesis. Mutations
 in the seed region of this microRNA cause familial keratoconus with cataract,
